The paper discusses a top-level ontology for representing and interchanging information on machine learning algorithms, datasets, and experiments. This falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of ontologies, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for better interpretability and interoperability of experiments, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
